                        <foliation ana="contemporary pag later fol">
                           <p>Paginated in the top margins and foliated in red ink in the bottom
                        right hand corners. Traces of an older foliation are occasionally visible next to the more recent one.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        
                        <condition ana="average">
                           <p>The manuscript begins and ends defective, and there are
                        lacunae after fols. <locus>1, 2, 15 and 22</locus>. The top and outer margins 
                              of most leaves have been cropped or are otherwise damaged,
                        sometimes with loss of text. Many of the bottom margins have been scraped
                        off, but some marginalia are still visible. Fols. <locus>24 and 25</locus>
                        have tears, the outer bottom corner of fol. <locus>29</locus> has been torn
                        away, and fol. <locus>34</locus> is blackened and damaged. The
                        script has been touched up with darker ink in some places.</p>
                        </condition>
                     
